properties.areaDesc: Northern Humboldt Coast; Southwestern Humboldt; Mendocino Coast; Coastal Del Norte
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued December 31 at 12:39PM PST until January 2 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT....A long period northwesterly swell will build late
tonight through Wednesday. This swell will bring a threat for
large breaking waves Wednesday morning through Thursday morning.
The largest breakers from 22 to 25 feet are expected on west and
northwest facing beaches Wednesday.

* WHERE...Coastal Del Norte, Northern Humboldt Coast,
Southwestern Humboldt and Mendocino Coast Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 AM Wednesday to 10 AM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Large breaking waves will generate hazardous
conditions on the beaches and harbor entrances. This threat
will be maximized on steeply sloped beaches. Large breaking
waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and rocks, and
capsize small boats near shore.
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area, producing rip currents and localized beach
erosion.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM WEDNESDAY TO 10 AM PST THURSDAY
